    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** serving as the undeniable anchor of the lineup. With an elite score of 75.26, his matchup against Feltner is the most favorable on the board, bolstered by a significant 14% park factor boost and a 15% skill edge against the opposing starter. Similarly, **Drake Baldwin** (60.73) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.38) capitalize on top-of-the-order positioning and favorable platoon dynamics. While we prioritize speed in this 5x5 format, the combination of **Jackson Merrill**\u2019s order placement and the offensive environment in his stadium makes him our highest-ceiling asset, particularly as we look to capitalize on the 13% platoon adjustment favoring his outlook today.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision landed on the bench, where **Josh Jung** (39.89) narrowly missed the final slot. Despite a solid base projection, **Josh Jung** was sidelined primarily due to an uncertain lineup status and a tough matchup against Bubba Chandler, which tempered his SP-skill adjustment. Meanwhile, the rotation is heavily impacted by the gauntlet of elite arms we face today; **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Marcell Ozuna** both face challenging outings against Joe Ryan and Jacob deGrom, respectively. While **Luis Robert Jr.** receives a slight bump for his ability to swipe bags against a slower delivery, the raw risk of facing deGrom drops **Marcell Ozuna**\u2019s utility efficiency significantly. We are keeping a close eye on the confirmed lineups for **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Marcell Ozuna**, as any shift downward in the batting order could necessitate a more conservative approach to preserve our games-played caps.",
